10 to strengthen the resilience and reliability of electric utility
11 services in the State, including helping review wildfire
12 mitigation plans of regulated public utilities.
13 SECTION 3. There is appropriated out of the public
14 utilities commission special fund established by section 269-33,
15 Hawaii Revised Statutes, the sum of $700,000 or so much thereof
16 as may be necessary for fiscal year 2024-2025 to contract
17 consultant services for utility dockets to assist with the
18 efforts to strengthen the resilience and reliability of electric
19 utility services in the State, including helping review wildfire
20 mitigation plans of regulated public utilities.
